verbs.description: vell (third-person singular simple present vells, present participle velling, simple past and past participle velled)

entries.meaning: (UK, dialect) To cut the turf from, as for burning.

description: Compare Latin vellus (“the skin of a sheep with the wool on it, a fleece, a hide or pelt”), or English fell (“a hide”).

entries.meaning: (UK, dialect) The salted stomach of a calf, used in making cheese; a rennet bag.
